cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computational Linguistics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with building a Part-of-Speech tagger for code-mixed Indian languages using Conditional Random Fields. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper mentions the use of a library called sklearn-crfsuite for training the model. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possibility as the paper deals with processing social media text. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possibility as the paper deals with natural language processing. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is less likely as the paper does not mention the use of neural networks or evolutionary algorithms.
